column5: Has anyone seen the new '08 Navionics chip for Canada? I am interested in how detailed the NW end of Lac Seul is. The '06 chip had very little detail in this area.
I got a msg from Jeff the other day... it may answer your question..https://www.walleyecentral.com/dc/dcb...4681&mode=full AC.

The last I heard Canada no longer allowed Navionic's to use their hydrographic charts. Lake Master has been charting Lake of the Wood's for new maps...www.lakemaster.com Not sure if they have done the Lac Suel area or not,,look at their site.. good luck, Mot

Does anyone know what vintage Navionics chips utilized the Canadian Government data. I will be traveling to Quebec and am curious if I might be able to track down a older chip with that detail. Thank you! RED
